The paper deals with facial feature detection from facial images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a hierarchical probabilistic model that learns the joint relationship among facial components, facial expression, and pose information through automatic structure learning and parameter estimation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
